<!-- Add Activity -->
    <activity>
       <introduction>
         <p>
             In the previous chapter, we introduced logarithms and explored their relationship
             with exponents. We also learned about the properties of logarithms and how to evaluate logarithmic 
             expressions. In this section, we will review these concepts and build a strong foundation
              for solving logarithmic equations in the upcoming sections.
         </p>
       </introduction>
        <statement>
            <p>
                <term>Work in groups</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                <term>What you need</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Paper</li>
                    <li>Pencil</li>
                    <li>Calculator (optional)</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>
                <term>What to do</term>
            </p>
        </statement>
    
    </activity>
    
